name: StyleExportTagMaps
shortdesc: A collection of style export tag maps.

parameter.name: withProperties
parameter.shortdesc: Initial values for properties of the new StyleExportTagMap &#40;Optional)

method.name: count
method.shortdesc: Displays the number of elements in the StyleExportTagMap.

method.name: item
method.shortdesc: Returns the StyleExportTagMap with the specified index or name.

parameter.name: index
parameter.shortdesc: The index or name. Can accept: Long Integer or String.

method.name: itemByRange
method.shortdesc: Returns the StyleExportTagMaps within the specified range.

parameter.name: from
parameter.shortdesc: The StyleExportTagMap, index, or name at the beginning of the range. Can accept: StyleExportTagMap, Long Integer or String.

parameter.name: to
parameter.shortdesc: The StyleExportTagMap, index, or name at the end of the range. Can accept: StyleExportTagMap, Long Integer or String.

method.name: firstItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the first StyleExportTagMap in the collection.

method.name: lastItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the last StyleExportTagMap in the collection.

method.name: middleItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the middle StyleExportTagMap in the collection.

method.name: previousItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the StyleExportTagMap with the index previous to the specified index.

parameter.name: obj
parameter.shortdesc: The index of the StyleExportTagMap that follows the desired StyleExportTagMap.

method.name: nextItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the StyleExportTagMap whose index follows the specified StyleExportTagMap in the collection.

parameter.name: obj
parameter.shortdesc: The StyleExportTagMap whose index comes before the desired StyleExportTagMap.

method.name: anyItem
method.shortdesc: Returns any StyleExportTagMap in the collection.

method.name: everyItem
method.shortdesc: Returns every StyleExportTagMap in the collection.

method.name: toSource
method.shortdesc: Generates a string which, if executed, will return the StyleExportTagMap.
Returns the StyleExportTagMap with the specified index.

property.name: length
property.shortdesc: The number of objects in the collection.
